olive oil
1 stalk celery
1 packet beef & pork mince
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
1 packet garlic paste
1 tsp honey
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet Baby Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Chargrilled Capsicum Relish
1 packet Garlic Aioli

• Thinly slice celery.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. Cook beef
& pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add chermoula spice blend and garlic paste and cook, stirring, until
fragrant, 1 minute.
• Remove from heat, add the honey and toss to combine. Season to taste.

• Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine shredded cabbage mix, celery,
baby leaves and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season with
salt and pepper.
• Microwave mini flourtortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts, until
warmed through.

• Spread chargrilled capsicum relish over tortillas, then top with slaw and
Middle Eastern-spiced beef and pork.
• Drizzle with garlic aioli to serve. Enjoy!